Program: The History Hour
Title: Nike and the Sweatshop Problem
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0w2
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 20 Aug 2017
On this week's programme, how campaigners took on Nike in the 1990s, plus the Turkish invasion of Cyprus and the newspaper which defied Argentine's military dictatorship. We also find out more about nudism in East Germany and the great Indian poet Rabindranath Tagore. PHOTO: Nike worker Cicih Sukaesih telling her story in America in 1996 (courtesy of Jeff Ballinger) Show less